programme.desc: Harper, a young nature photographer on an assignment in the woods of the Watchatoomy valley, captures a disturbing event where a man was brutally whipped and beaten. programme.title: Missing 1
programme.desc: Hyeon-jeong's sister is missing and she fears for the worst. Via her sister's cell phone, Hyeon-jeong learns that her sister had been staying in a countryside village. She goes to the village to find her sister and stops at the local police station for help. Because of the little evidence she has, the police refuse to offer help. Hyeong-jeong then finds a witness who thinks she saw her missing sister near the home of an elderly man Pan-kon. When Hyeong-jeong eventually arrives at the elderly man's home, her worst nightmares are to begin.

programme.title: Dark House

But when he does his walk-through of the latest house, he finds Christine, a squatter who claims that she just cannot leave the premises - the house will not let her! Paul tries to show her just how easy it is to leave but finds that he is now trapped, too. As the night wears on the two of them are forced to confront apparitions and hallucinations connected to their lives and the choices they have made. Now, they must face their fears and find a way to escape, otherwise they will be trapped forever in their own private purgatory.

programme.title: Iliana
programme.desc: Feodor is at the opening of a gallery exhibition when he is struck by the ethereal beauty of Iliana and they connect in front of the painting titled "A Polyanitsa's Smile". Little did they expect that the story behind the painting would be a reflection of their fate. Years later they meet again, after married life has taken a toll on Iliana and the passion between them had long cooled. Feodor is disturbed by the shift in her personality. Then, Iliana invites their mutual friends, Igor and Margarita, to a casual dinner at home. During dinner we discover Margarita is one of Feodor's many lovers, and we realize there was a purpose in bringing them together. As the tension grows, someone puts up cameras to watch the situation unfold...

programme.title: Amulet
programme.desc: Cela, a magazine writer on male - female relationships, is having trouble with his own girlfriend. The problem is that he has an eye for the ladies. When his girlfriend catches him with another girl, he is promptly kicked out of their apartment. Broke and homeless, he finds an old woman willing to rent out a room in her old, delapidated house. Cela is initially put off by the inhospitable living conditions, but then the other tenant, a beautiful girl, catches his eye - and breath. He changes his mind and decides to stay, unaware of how much trouble he is getting himself into.

programme.title: Lechmi
programme.desc: Vineeth, Ikku, Stephen and Sudhi are four carefree young men sharing a flat in a little town in Kerala. One night, their lives are turned upside down by the sudden appearance of a pretty young female ghost. Lechmi is a sweet soul but try as she might, she cannot remember her real name, where she came from, or how she died. Initially scared witless, the four young men later enlist the help of Baba Swami, an exorcist, to find out more about Lechmi. Behind the humorous banter interspersed with chilling scenes of ghostly encounters, is a pressing message about the safety of young women in India, and the damaging psychological effects on the victims of assault.

A series of weird things happen right after he arrives. Visions of a mysterious wounded girl, people with marks from strange surgeries, people disappearing mysteriously. All this is made worse by a traditional healer who rejects modern medicine. The myths abound in the village lead Rian to think something sinister is afoot. Afraid of being alone, he invites his two best friends from Jakarta to stay and observe the goings-on. When the truth is finally revealed, the cost is brutal in the heart of the deep and dark forest of Kalimantan.

And the only ones who can stop the doll's killing spree are Dimas and Jean.
